// Syncthing ignore list for ~/dev
// Synced across machines (p14, t580, zandvoort) so the same exclusions apply
// everywhere. macOS-Linux platform mismatch makes some entries non-optional
// (native binaries under node_modules will NOT work cross-platform).

// ─── Build outputs (always-regenerable, often huge) ─────────────────────
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.nuxt
**/.turbo
**/.vite
**/.svelte-kit
**/.angular
**/.expo
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/target            // Rust
**/.cargo            // local cargo cache
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.tox
**/.venv
**/venv
**/.gradle
**/.dart_tool
**/coverage
**/.coverage
**/.nyc_output

// ─── Package manager state (per-machine / per-arch) ─────────────────────
**/.pnpm-store
**/.yarn/cache
**/.yarn/install-state.gz
**/.bun
**/.npm
**/.local-chromium

// ─── Git transient files (mid-operation, would corrupt other clones) ────
**/.git/index.lock
**/.git/objects/pack/tmp_*
**/.git/HEAD.lock

// ─── direnv / asdf / mise caches ────────────────────────────────────────
**/.envrc.cache
**/.direnv

// ─── Editor / IDE per-machine state ─────────────────────────────────────
**/.idea/workspace.xml
**/.idea/shelf
**/.idea/usage.statistics.xml
**/.vscode/.ropeproject
**/.history

// ─── macOS cruft (would litter Linux machines) ──────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
**/._*
**/.AppleDouble
**/.LSOverride
**/.fseventsd
**/.Spotlight-V100
**/.Trashes
**/.VolumeIcon.icns
**/.DocumentRevisions-V100
**/.TemporaryItems
**/.com.apple.timemachine.donotpresent

// ─── Windows cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/Thumbs.db
**/ehthumbs.db

// ─── General junk ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.pid
**/*.sock
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*.log.gz

// ─── Syncthing internal artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────
**/.syncthing.*.tmp
**/*.sync-conflict-*
